== What's this? ==

A stupid script to generate fake italian email addresses.
We use them for honeypot on lugbs.linux.it domain.
Names and surnames are real and human checked.

== Can I help you? ==

Of course! There are a lot of things to do!
You can write me to: andrea.gelmini@lugbs.linux.it

== Screenshots ==

gelma@vaio:~/dev/prg/FakeItalianEmails$ ./fakeitalianemails.py --help
fakeitalianemails.py creates *real* fake italian email addresses
Usage: fakeitalianemails.py [OPTIONS]

OPTIONS are:
	-d, --domain     specify domain name to use (you can submit more domains separeted by space)
	-n, --number     specify how many addresses to create
	-w, --web        output as HTML comment

Example:
	./fakeitalianemails.py -n 10 -d 'example.com lugbs.linux.it'

	Ubaldo.rizzotti@lugbs.linux.it
	Caci.giovbattista@example.com
	nigro-clateo.46@example.com
	nazario_Tognascioli@lugbs.linux.it
	Girando-castaniere@lugbs.linux.it
